ZH: 昨天我突然失神，差点儿晕倒。
EN: Yesterday, I suddenly felt dizzy and almost fainted.

ZH: 她在考试过程中突然失神，无法继续答题。
EN: She suddenly lost consciousness during the exam and was unable to continue answering questions.

ZH: 他因为血糖偏低而失神了。
EN: He fainted because of low blood sugar.

ZH: 她常常在午后感到倦倦欲睡，有时甚至失神。
EN: She often feels tired and even loses consciousness in the afternoon.

ZH: 高温天气容易导致人们失神。
EN: High temperatures can easily cause people to faint.

ZH: 当他听到坏消息时，他感到失神。
EN: He felt dizzy when he heard the bad news.

ZH: 突然变暗的教室让学生感到失神。
EN: The sudden darkness in the classroom made the students feel dizzy.

ZH: 长时间不吃东西容易导致低血糖，从而引起失神。
EN: Not eating for a long time can easily lead to low blood sugar, causing fainting.

ZH: 晕船很容易导致人们失神。
EN: Getting seasick can easily make people faint.

ZH: 他暴露在强光下太久了，结果居然失神了。
EN: He was exposed to bright light for too long and ended up fainting.

ZH: 某些药物副作用会引起失神。
EN: Some medication side effects can cause fainting.

ZH: 大量出汗会导致失神。
EN: Sweating heavily can lead to fainting.

ZH: 这个运动项目要求耐力较高，如果没注意饮食，就很容易失神。
EN: This sport requires a high endurance level, and if you don't pay attention to your diet, it's easy to faint.

ZH: 突然站立可以引起立位性失神。
EN: Standing up suddenly can cause orthostatic fainting.

ZH: 血压突然下降会导致失神。
EN: Sudden drop in blood pressure can lead to fainting.

ZH: 女性在经期可能会经历血糖波动，导致失神。
EN: Women may experience blood sugar fluctuations during menstruation, leading to fainting.

ZH: 持续过长的剧烈运动可能会导致失神。
EN: Prolonged intense exercise can lead to fainting.

ZH: 高血糖也可能导致人们失神。
EN: High blood sugar can also cause people to faint.

ZH: 此药可能会引起头晕和失神。
EN: This medication may cause dizziness and fainting.

ZH: 长时间坐着不动会导致人们失神。
EN: Sitting still for a long time can lead to fainting.
